description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an excellent opportunity for an talented individual within our Care of the Elderly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our aim is to bring your ambition to life. This role will take a lead focus on Elderly Care and Orthogeriatric care. Our Medical Consultant workforce are supported to develop a specialist interest, such as TIA, Stroke or Parkinson’s Disease (for discussion at interview). We have a protected training budget for medical staff which will support your development, and a focus on career development for medics at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently one of the highest performing Trusts in Greater Manchester, with a number of award winning and pioneering initiatives. We are currently developing our Frailty and our Surgical Liaison agenda, and we need forward-thinking people to help us create our vision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your experience and vision will be supported by our skilled team of clinical staff alongside dedicated and trained nurses. You will be able to contribute to training/teaching, our leadership agenda and audit and other Clinical Governance activity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would also consider supporting an experienced middle grade into this role through the CESR route&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will also be expected to participate in the Medicine on call rota with a commitment of 1:14.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ema O&#39;Neill-Jones, Directorate Manager&lt;br /&gt;0161 922 4105&lt;/p&gt;
